B may merge\nand form one of the largest bound systems in the nearby Universe. Another part\nof the CB, with the cluster Gr2064, will form a separate system. The structures\nwith a current density contrast $\\Delta\\rho \\approx 30$ have passed turnaround\nand started to collapse at redshifts $z \\approx 0.3 - 0.4$. The comparison of\nthe number and properties of the most massive collapsing supercluster cores\nfrom observations and simulations may serve as a test for cosmological models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Mar 2021 11:07:29 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Mar 2021 09:11:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-12"}
